a million dollars or zero dollars.'' <PERSON> Michelle </PERSON> <PERSON> Valentine </PERSON>, the young <LOCATION> Virginia </LOCATION> woman adopting a baby girl with AIDS, told the commission she is having trouble getting permission to take in a second child. `` You're single, we ca n't consider you,'' she said she has been told. Then, in exasperation, she said: `` The typical young yuppie couple wants one of these kids like they want a hole in the head.'' <PERSON> Smithies </PERSON> said child placement agencies should rethink the family criteria they use when placing children with AIDS. She cited instances, for example, `` where gay men have been absolutely extraordinary as care givers.'' `` We have to expand our vision of what a family is,'' <PERSON> Abrams </PERSON> added. The three women were among 14 witnesses heard by the commission during the first of four days of hearings this month.
