onnel. The country's <ORGANIZATION> Catholic </ORGANIZATION> leader, Archbishop <PERSON> Marcos </PERSON> <PERSON> McGrath </PERSON>, has been asked by President <PERSON> Oscar </PERSON> <PERSON> Arias </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Costa </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Rica </LOCATION> and Prime Minister <PERSON> Felipe </PERSON> <PERSON> Gonzalez </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Spain </LOCATION> to mediate an end to <LOCATION> Panama </LOCATION>'s crisis But the government has accused <PERSON> McGrath </PERSON> of siding with the opposition. State-run newspapers have called the archbishop, who was born in <LOCATION> Philadelphia </LOCATION>, a `` tool of the <ORGANIZATION> Yankees </ORGANIZATION>.''
