soned at <LOCATION> Soledad </LOCATION>, where he has since been denied parole numerous times since he first became eligible to apply for parole in 1975. `` The <ORGANIZATION> LAPD </ORGANIZATION> investigation into the <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> F. </PERSON> <PERSON> Kennedy </PERSON> assassination by <PERSON> Sirhan </PERSON> <PERSON> Sirhan </PERSON> was exhaustive, yet public concern about its conclusions remains 20 years later,'' <PERSON> Eu </PERSON> said in a written statement released by her office. `` In light of that concern, we believe the public's right know generally outweighs privacy concerns, and have governed our public release of these materials with that guideline.'' The files include reports of investigations of specific conspiracy theories _ <PERSON> Sirhan </PERSON> has since said he acted alone in killing <PERSON> Kennedy </PERSON> _ and audio and video tapes from the crime scene. The material has been stored in <LOCATION> Sacramento </LOCATION> since last August, under an agreement between <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION> and the state. The agreement followed a lengthy effort by scholars and other interested persons to persuade <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION> police officials not to keep the material secret.
