 Scientists have uncovered genetic characteristics of people by analyzing single strands of their hair, a significant step in using high technology to solve crimes, researchers say. The technique can help show that a suspect was at a crime scene where a hair has been found, said <PERSON> Russell </PERSON> <PERSON> Higuchi </PERSON> of <ORGANIZATION> Cetus </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, <LOCATION> Emeryville </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Calif </LOCATION>. He and colleague <PERSON> Henry </PERSON> <PERSON> Erlich </PERSON> describe the work in Thursday's issue of the British journal Nature with <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Sensabaugh </PERSON> and <PERSON> Cecilia </PERSON> <PERSON> von </PERSON> <PERSON> Beroldingen </PERSON> of the <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> California </ORGANIZATION> at <LOCATION> Berkeley </LOCATION>
