<BYLINE>AP Business Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Food and tobacco giant <ORGANIZATION> RJR </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nabisco </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> has fired a longtime advertising agency, and one source familiar with the decision said it reflected <ORGANIZATION> RJR </ORGANIZATION>'s displeasure over the agency's no-smoking ads for another client <ORGANIZATION> RJR </ORGANIZATION> cited recent philosophical differences Tuesday for its decision to dismiss the ad agency <ORGANIZATION> Saatchi </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <ORGANIZATION> Saatchi </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> DFS </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, and declined to elaborate. But a source familiar with the decision said <ORGANIZATION> RJR </ORGANIZATION> was displeased at the ads <PERSON> Saatchi </PERSON> recently developed to tout <ORGANIZATION> Northwest </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION>' new no-smoking program Industry sources estimate the agency was handling as much as $ 100 million in ad billings for <ORGANIZATION> RJR </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nabisco </ORGANIZATION> candy, cookies and chewing gum, making it a major account by ad industry standards. In announcing the dismissal in a statement from <LOCATION> Atlanta </LOCATION>, the company said, `` It is important as <ORGANIZATION> RJR </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nabisco </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> shapes and executes its marketing and sales objectives it deals with advertising agencies that have a wholly-consistent philosophical approach to its plans and programs.'' `` During this important period, philosophical differences have developed between <ORGANIZATION> RJR </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nabisco </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> and one of its agencies, <ORGANIZATION> Saatchi </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <ORGANIZATION> Saatchi </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATI