<DATELINE>EAGAN, Minn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Northwest </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION> announced a two-month discount that will give senior citizens a percentage off their fare that matches their age. For example, a 65-year-old will receive a 65 percent discount and a 100-year-old will fly free, the airline said Tuesday. `` The stock phrase, ` I'm not getting older, just better,' deserves an updating,'' said A.B. <PERSON> Magary </PERSON>, executive vice president of marketing for <ORGANIZATION> Northwest </ORGANIZATION>. `` The older you are the greater your discount gets.'' The discount, which covers people aged 65 and older, is good from April 12 through June 8 and applies to all full economy fares on <ORGANIZATION> Northwest </ORGANIZATION>'s domestic flights. The fares may be used every day except Fridays and Sundays and May 31, and reservations must be made and tickets purchased at least seven days in advance. Travel must include at least two nights' stay before returning and must be concluded by June 8. <PERSON> Magary </PERSON> said the idea is to stimulate discretionary travel until the peak summer season begins in June. With that goal in mind, <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Continental </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION> _ both subsidiaries of giant <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> _ announced Tuesday that they are reducing fares for the next two months on tickets carrying restrictions used mainly by vacationers. <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION> made similar fare cuts. <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION>'s `` spring sales'' are for travel between April 18 and June 15, with no one-way fare greater than $ 99 for travel anywhere in the mainla