<HEAD>Turner Property To Be Sold At Auction</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ORLANDO, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The Feds are finally getting <PERSON> Glenn </PERSON> <PERSON> Turner </PERSON>'s castle A federal court and the <ORGANIZATION> Internal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Revenue </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION> have begun foreclosure proceedings on the three-story, long-uncompleted castle owned by the hillbilly entrepreneur who made and lost a fortune by selling motivational-training and cosmetics franchises in the 1970s. The <ORGANIZATION> IRS </ORGANIZATION> has been trying for 10 years to collect a $ 15 million back-taxes claim against <PERSON> Turner </PERSON>, 53, who was in and out of trouble with the law for years because of what investigators said were illegal pyramid schemes that defrauded thousands of investors. He is currently serving a seven-year prison term in <LOCATION> Arizona </LOCATION> on fraud convictions. Now, one of his prized possessions, the 16-room castle and 79 surrounding acres on <LOCATION> Bear </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Gulley </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Lake </LOCATION> in neighboring <LOCATION> Seminole </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Fla. </LOCATION>, is being sold at auction to satisfy an <ORGANIZATION> IRS </ORGANIZATION> judgment against him in <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> District </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Orlando </LOCATION>. But the <ORGANIZATION> IRS </ORGANIZATION> figures it will be lucky to get even a fraction of the final amount set by the court: $ 9.275 million. The estate was appraised by the county at $ 1.13 million in 1987, and recent appraisals by private companies list its value at between $ 1.6 million and $ 2 million. Senior <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> District Judge <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Young </PERSON> will hold a hearing April 26 to decide if two bids for the property _ or any new ones made in the interim _ will be accepted. Once the property is sold, <LOCATION> Seminole </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> has the right to be paid first from the proceeds. County Tax Collector <PERSON> G. </PERSON> <PERSON> Troy </PERSON> <PERSON> Ray </PERSON> said about $ 16,900 in unpaid property taxes is owed on the property for 1987. <PERSON> Turner </PERSON> and his family have n't paid property taxes since 1979, but private investors have bought tax certificates equal to the back taxes each year. Under such an arrangement, the investors pay the taxes and earn 18 percent interest until the property is sold and the tax funds are paid back to them. Those tax payments will come from the sale, too. Court documents indicate there are dozens of other Turner creditors, but it is unlikely that they will be paid until all of the <ORGANIZATION> IRS </ORGANIZATION> judgment is satisfied, officials said. Bids on the Castle property will be advertised over the next few weeks to notify any potential bidders of the pending sale. Besides the castle, there is a boathouse with a three-bedroom apartment and a stable. The castle and boathouse have been vacant for several years, and the castle has been used only for tours and charitable events. Turner's financial empire crumbled in 1973 after he reportedly made about $ 300 million through aggressive marketing of his Orlando-based Dare To Be Great motivational classes and <PERSON> Koscot </PERSON> cosmetics distributorships. The self-styled country boy, son of a <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Carolina </LOCATION> sharecropper, rose to fame through inspirational speeches that promised great wealth if people bought distributorships in his operations. The companies collapsed under lawsuits filed by investors and investigations by state and federal agencies. <PERSON> Turner </PERSON> and a longtime partner, <PERSON> Edward </PERSON> <PERSON> Rector </PERSON>, 57, were sentenced to prison in <LOCATION> Arizona </LOCATION> on charges of operating a pyramid scheme there and defrauding investors through a later self-motivational company called <ORGANIZATION> Challenge </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc </ORGANIZATION>.
