. 1, 1989, and the $ 143 million is the estimated worth over five years. `` The <LOCATION> Pennsylvania </LOCATION> Lottery system will be the newest and most powerful lottery system available to the lottery industry today,'' said <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> Chidester </PERSON>, vice president of wagering services for the Automated Wagering Division. <ORGANIZATION> Control </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Data </ORGANIZATION>, with over 50 percent of the market for on-line lottery equipment, supplies lotteries in five states besides <LOCATION> Pennsylvania </LOCATION> and recently was awarded the contract for <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION>'s new lottery, the company said The other states with <ORGANIZATION> Control </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Data </ORGANIZATION> equipment are <LOCATION> Maryland </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Delaware </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Illinois </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>.
